76 Corlett Drive is a 3 storey state-of-the-art office development coming up in Melrose North, a suburb of Johannesburg, South Africa. Also Read:Â IKUSASA Office Block development at Oxford Park, South Africa With a total gross floor area of 2167 m2, the 76 Corlett drive development features two storeys of usable space and a rooftop urban farm. It also features a 1731 m2 car park area with the capacity to accommodate approximately 105 cars. The parking area is fitted with electric car charging stations, and it also offers ample bicycle stations and convenient showering facilities for cyclists and runners.  The exterior of the cubic 76 Corlett Drive building is a mix of vertical gardens and sun-controlling aluminum, designed to allow as much natural light on the inside as possible while using a smart cooling system that is energy efficient. 76 Corlett Drive is set to achieve the highest possible rated green star building in South Africa, net-zero ratings for waste, energy, water, land-use and ecology categories, and living building challenge. Owner: Legaro Properties Electrical Engineer: Rawlins Wales Pty Ltdt/A Pwp Taemane Consulting Engineers Quantity Surveyors: Deheyder Noppe And Partners, and Legaro Properties Architects: Daffonchio & Associates Architects Mechanical Engineer: Graeme Page Consulting Engineers Main Contractor: Legaro Properties Project Manager: Legaro Properties Sustainable Building Consultant: Solid Green Consulting Wet Services: Ajc Plumbing Structural Engineers: Kantey & Templer Fire Engineer: Ife Sa International Fire Engineering Lift Specialist: Kone Elevators South Africa (Pty) Ltd Environmental Consultant: Leap Landscape Architect Environmental Planner Waste Contractor: Kendis Bhekamina Demolishers